The Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps have found the corpse of a 55-year-old man identified as ISYAKU SHUAIBU along Kiyawa- Andaza road in Kiyawa local Government. NSCDC spokesman CSC Adamu Shehu stated this in a statement issued to DAILY POST. He said the deceased who is from Shuwari Town in Kiyawa LGA was found dead yesterday at about 0930HRS. He said the distress call was received by the Command and a team from the Medical Unit was immediately deployed. He said the dead body was recovered by the roadside, just about Two (2) kilometres away from Aandaza town. Adamu said preliminary examinations at the scene shows no sign of physical injury or bruises and the body was taken to the General Hospital, Dutse for post- mortem. He said the State Commandant Mustpha Talba has ordered the deployment of Intelligence officers to conduct thorough investigations in the Area. He urged the residents not to panic as all efforts to unravel the mysterious death.